**Documentation Standards:**
- Generate documentation for new features by extending README.md
- Add comments in code explaining reasoning for non-obvious implementations
- Document complex logic and business rules inline
- Update relevant documentation when modifying existing features
- Include usage examples for new functionality
- Document configuration options and environment variables
- Maintain clear setup and installation instructions
- Add troubleshooting sections for common issues
- Keep documentation up-to-date with code changes
- Use clear, concise language and proper formatting
- Include diagrams or flowcharts for complex processes when helpful